reviewText: One of the funniest shojo animes out there.

A good series as always, but as always it still feels too short and cuts off at an odd time. If anything, this season felt a little more scattered with the story line it was trying to tell than the first one, as if it didn't know where it wanted to focus.
I hope there's a season 3 that will make it's way to the USA.

I loved the first season and the second held all of the same magic!

Season 2 of Kamisama Kiss was a lot of fun to watch and a great continuation of the series after Season 1. I have not watched the Subtitled Version of the show yet but the English voice cast was great and did a really good job of bringing the characters to life. I also really enjoyed listing to the commentated episodes in special features and hearing what the voice actors had to say about the show and their characters. I hope to see more of this series released as anime.

I haven't bought this yet, but I'm going to!!! Kamisama Kiss/ Kamisama Hajimemashita how ever you want to pronounce it, I prefer Kamisama Hajimemashita. Is a wonderful series filled with amazing charaters. I have also purchased the mangas. The storyline is amazing!!! I honestly disliked how the second season ended. But hopefully the'll decided to do a third season!!! I defiantly recommend this anime to anyone, especially if your into comedy/romance series. I love, love, love... LOVE this show!!!  which is weird that I like it I'm a Christian who believes in God!!! And not other gods!!! But this is an anime it's not real... Tomoe and Nanami are perfect for each other!!! Please release a third season thank you!!!

Poorly animated. I love the manga, but the animation in this is unacceptable. It might as well be a slide show for the manga. I also feel the writing is poorly done, so if you haven't read the manga there is no way you could understand what is going on.

Chose standard shipping at checkout and it arrived in only two days, in great condition - no dents or any kind of damage. The show itself is amazing! The voices match the characters perfectly, the animation is beautiful. I was a little disappointed that it ended without wrapping up everything in the manga, but there's nothing they could do about it if it's not renewed for a third season. It will make a lot more sense if you read the manga first! Immediately after finishing both seasons, I watched them over again because I loved it so much. Definitely recommend!
